        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 2:08PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 207 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northwest of Murphy, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hiawasse Dam, Violet, and Unaka.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
